7 COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
8 An Act relating to behavioral health; defining terms;
directing the Medicaid program to expand services;
9 providing scope of practice for behavioral health
clinical interns; requiring behavioral health interns
10 to comply with all administrative requirements;
providing for codification; and providing an
11 effective date.
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 15-101 of Title 43A, unless
17 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 As used in this section:
19 1. "Behavioral health clinical intern" means a graduate student
20 enrolled in a nationally accredited clinical training program that
21 meets minimum credentials for service provided or code billed;
22 2. "Clinical training program" means programs of study that are
23 nationally accredited master's or doctoral programs preparing
24 students for the licensed marriage and family therapist (LMFT),
Req. No. 16600 Page 1

1 lice nsed professional counselor (LPC), licensed clinical social
2 worker (LCSW), licensed alcohol and drug counselor (LADC), or
3 psychologist state licensures to practice;
4 3. "Licensed behavioral health provider" means a behavioral
5 health professional that is a licensed professional counselor (LPC),
6 licensed family and marital therapist (LFMT), licensed behavioral
7 practitioner (LBP), licensed clinical social worker (LCSW), licensed
8 alcohol and drug counselor (LADC), or licensed psychologist; and
9 4. "Nationally accredited program" means that the training
10 program has met all training standards to hold an active
11 accreditation aligned with the discipline of study, including but
12 not limited to, the Commission on Accreditation for Marriage and
13 Family Therapy Education (COAMFTE), the Council for Accreditation of
14 Counseling and Related Educational Programs (CACREP), the Council on
15 Social Work Education (CSWE), or the American Psychological
16 Association (APA).
17 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 15-102 of Title 43A, unless
19 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 The Oklahoma Medicaid Plan administrator shall expand services
21 by adding a provider code for master's and doctoral level behavioral
22 health clinical interns.
23 Behavioral health clinical intern providers shall only provide
24 services billable through clinical sites that are accredited in good
Req. No. 16600 Page 2

1 stan ding with behavioral health services site accreditations such
2 as: the Commission on Accreditation of Rehabilitation Facilities
3 (CARF), The Joint Commission, the American Society of Addiction
4 Medicine (ASAM) Level of Care Certification, program certification
5 through the Oklahoma Department of Mental Health and Substance Abuse
6 Services, the Council on Accreditation (COA) or other national
7 behavioral health service site accrediting body.
8 Behavioral health clinical interns may provide services within
9 their clinical scope of practice under the on-site supervision of a
10 licensed behavioral health provider. On-site supervisors may only
11 supervise six (6) or fewer behavioral health clinical interns at any
12 time.
13 Behavioral health clinical interns shall comply with all
14 registration, training, documentation, and protocols required of
15 other behavioral health providers in the Oklahoma Medicaid plan.
16 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
